New York Mets Owners May Face More Bernie Madoff-Related Woes, WSJ Says

-- B y   M i k e   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-03-03T02:04:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/mets-owners-may-face-more-madoff-related-woes-wsj-says.html
New York Mets owners Fred Wilpon and
Saul Katz, who already face a $1 billion lawsuit related to
withdrawals from  Bernard Madoff ’s investment firm, may have more
allegations coming their way from court-appointed trustee  Irving
Picard  if they don’t reach a settlement, the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
situation.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Millard at 
 mmillard2@bloomberg.net  